##The number of confirmed cases in the United States has risen to 163, and the death rate is far higher than in other countries, Donald Trump said.

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

As of Friday afternoon local time, there were 163 confirmed cases in 18 states, according to the New York Times'tally of new cases reported by state public health authorities. Washington state public health authorities announced a death case Friday, bringing the total number of deaths in the United States to 12.

The death rate in the United States is 6.96 percent, more than double the world average of 3.4 percent and far higher than in China, the data show.

3.4% global fatality rate for newly diagnosed pneumonia?

DONALD TRUMP: "I'd say less than 1% . " 

Who director-general Tan Desai said on the 3rd, the current world has 3.4% of new cases of pneumonia reported deaths, higher than the previous forecast of 2.1% . He also highlighted the difference between pneumonia and seasonal flu, which typically kills less than 1% of the population. There is no vaccine for NCP, and the number of infections and severe cases increases.

However, just as the World Health Organization organization announced a global fatality rate of 3.4% for newly diagnosed pneumonia, Donald Trump went public with a "gut feeling" : fake. "I'd say less than 1 percent, " he said, referring to new crown pneumonia as "new crown flu. ".

In a telephone interview with Fox News Channel on Thursday night, Donald Trump complained to host Shawn Grant Hanley that the WHO's numbers were "fake. " He called the new pneumonia "new crown flu" and said the reported death rate from the infection is so high that many people do not need to go to a doctor to recover from the infection.

At present, all of the 11 new pneumonia deaths in the United States are in the West Coast states of Washington (10) and California (1) . A state of emergency has been declared in both states.

Since the outbreak on American soil, Donald Trump has gone from initially promising to be "well prepared and very low risk" to accusing Democrats and the media of "exaggerating the epidemic and panicking the market" , then there is the admission that the situation "could get worse" , the question of "can a vaccine be made in two months" , and finally the blame for the US's lack of virus detection capabilities on Obama's predecessor.

The American public, already unhappy with his performance, took the comment further. At Vox, Allons Rupar, an American journalist, described Donald Trump's claim as "shockingly irresponsible" , saying he did not know the difference between a new coronary and a flu.

Fossey, the US National Director of Allergy and Institute of Medical Science, also warned Donald Trump that the new pneumonia was "more deadly than the traditional flu" .

As of Friday afternoon local time, the United States has 163 confirmed cases, distributed in 18 states. With the spread of the epidemic, the United States has also introduced a number of state response measures.

California declared a state of emergency Thursday. CDC announced the same day to expand the scope of new coronaviruses test subjects, doctors can be based on clinical diagnosis to determine whether patients need nucleic acid testing.

United States relaxes testing conditions for new coronavirus

The United States Centers for Disease Control and Prevention announced Thursday that it will again relax the conditions for testing for the new coronavirus, allowing patients with fever, cough and dyspnea to be tested for the new coronavirus nucleic acid after doctors approve the test.

The NUCLEIC ACID test kits sent out by the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and prevention this week can test 75,000 people, U.S. secretary of Health and Human Services Alex Azar said in an interview Thursday, cDC Contractors are shipping test kits to hospitals and laboratories for more than a million tests.

The US state of California declared a state of emergency Thursday in response to a new outbreak of pneumonia. According to the announcement, the state of emergency will make it easier for the California government to access emergency supplies and ensure that county and city governments share information to help prevent and control the outbreak, in accordance with emergency regulations and plans.

An important reason for the state of emergency in California was the first death in the state on the morning of the 4th. The case was aboard the Princess Royal, which is now en route to San Francisco, and 21 people on board are said to have developed symptoms. The California government has now ordered the ship out of port and will send emergency crews to board and inspect the ship.

According to the latest figures released by the California government, as of the evening of 4,53 new cases of pneumonia in California, more than 9,400 people in home quarantine.

Foreign media: The United States epidemic data error, may miss a large number of cases of infection

Because the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention only focuses on inbound travelers and screens imported cases, it has not expanded the scope of testing and may miss a large number of infections, according to a report on the website of the Atlantic monthly on the 3rd.

The article said that the United States has now appeared non-imported cases, proof of the epidemic into the "community transmission" phase. Trevor Bedford, a computational biologist at the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center in Seattle, Washington, says there is "strong evidence" that the new coronavirus has been circulating in the state for at least several weeks. However, the number of Americans who have been tested is very limited.

The article points out that while other countries are taking massive measures to control the epidemic, the U.S. public health authorities are staring at the surface data and saying that the epidemic is likely to spread in the United States, while they are standing still.

The French "Echo" recently reported that the United States at this stage of the new coronavirus detection measures are ineffective. The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention is lagging behind the epidemic in large-scale testing. The kits used by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention have also been shown to be defective, requiring urgent production of new products.

Reported that the United States testing efficiency is also unsatisfactory, the current average of 10,000 tests per day in South Korea, the United States, the average number of tests only a few hundred times. U. S. officials have not yet released a list of health care facilities available to the public for testing. In addition, the high cost of health care in the United States could be a major obstacle to the prevention and control of the new coronavirus. Many people may choose to delay reporting or hide symptoms because of concerns about the cost of in high spirits's testing and treatment.
